  <p>
A function <m>f\colon \mathcal{S}^n\to \mathcal{S}</m> is
called <em>logical</em> if there is a function <m>g\colon \B^n \to
  \B</m> so
that <m>g(v(p_1),v(p_1),\ldots,v(p_n))=v(f(p_1,p_1,\ldots,p_n))</m> for
all <m>n</m>-tuples of statements <m>p_1,p_2,\ldots,p_n</m>.
</p>
